    {
      "id": "mnsik922",
      "questionNumber": 7,
      "questionText": "<p>Shown below is the structure of methyl acetate with three different $\\alpha, \\beta$ and $\\gamma$ carbon - oxygen bonds.</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 8 English\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mnt37ry9/16636331-dc2f-4918-a42d-8e390fdedcfa/afca2b10-34f5-11f1-a0ba-554d230e3732/file-6y3zli1mnt37rya.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mnt37ry9/16636331-dc2f-4918-a42d-8e390fdedcfa/afca2b10-34f5-11f1-a0ba-554d230e3732/file-6y3zli1mnt37rya.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>The correct order of bond lengths of these bonds is :</p>",
      "options": [
        "<p>$$ \\alpha>\\beta>\\gamma $$</p>\n",
        "<p>$$ \\alpha<\\beta<\\gamma $$</p>\n",
        "<p>$$ \\alpha=\\beta=\\gamma $$</p>\n",
        "<p>$$ \\alpha<\\beta=\\gamma $$</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 1,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "electron-displacement-effect",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 8 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mobqb2wn/b6833413-8485-4979-90ef-c39df81784de/1956f870-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqb2wo.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mobqb2wn/b6833413-8485-4979-90ef-c39df81784de/1956f870-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqb2wo.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Evening Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 8 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mobqb3gw/a743e524-eedf-449e-a7ea-82648e8d9f84/19c63500-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqb3gx.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mobqb3gw/a743e524-eedf-449e-a7ea-82648e8d9f84/19c63500-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqb3gx.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p><p>Resonance structure (I) is more stable than (II) due to being neutral than the othere charged structure. $c=0$ is shorter than $c-0$ bond due to double bond character. $\\beta$ is shorter than $\\gamma$ die to partial double bond chanacter.</p><p></p>\n<p>Order : $\\quad \\alpha&lt;\\beta&lt;\\gamma$</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
